== English ==
*''Day of the Week:'' '''Sunday'''
**'''Last:''' [[Saturday]] (of the previous week)
**'''Next:''' [[Monday]]
----

=== Pronunciation ===
[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"sVndei/<br>
[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈsʌndeɪ/

=== Etymology ===
From Middle English, from Old English [[sunnandæg]].

===[[Noun]]===

#The seventh day of the week in Europe and in systems using the ISO 8601 norm.
#The first [[day]] of the [[week]] in the USA.
#The "venerable day of the sun", as declared by Roman Emperor Constantine on March 7, AD 321.
Put simply, it follows [[Saturday]] and precedes [[Monday]] and is the [[sabbath]] for most [[Christian]]s.
#An appointment, person, or feeling associated with this day of the week.

